Can you please use the following code instead:
        String batchId;
        try (CloseableClientResponse response = getResponse(RequestType.POST, "upload")) {
            assertEquals(Status.CREATED.getStatusCode(), response.getStatus());
            JsonNode node = mapper.readTree(response.getEntityInputStream());
            batchId = node.get("batchId").getValueAsText();
            assertNotNull(batchId);
        }

The /upload/new/{handler} endpoint only makes sense when specifying a handler other than the default one (S3 for instance).
The fact that the /upload endpoint is marked as deprecated in the documentation is a mistake and should be fixed...

